On Tue, 16 Apr 2002, Tom wrote:

> Considering replacing the oil pump in my 75 2000cc. Oil pressure is just
> not right and the pump is the only thing that wasn't replaced during the
> rebuild. So I ask once again for advice before I proceed.
> 
> 1. Has anyone used any of the aftermarket oil pumps on the pancake
> engine? Results good/bad? Longevity? Currently looking into CB
> Performance but looking for suggestions.

when I rebuilt my 2L a few years ago I used a new Melling high capacity
pump and honed it in before installation.  this is a stock pump for the 2L

get great presure and volume

> 2. Is it possible to change the pump without pulling the engine?
> Eyeballing says if I remove the tin on the back of the engine I should
> be able to remove the alternator, fan and housing to access the pump.

in theory yes, in practice PITA

